Web?topicID=934.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   At what level is it worthwhile to maintain all four pets?</span><hr size=1> I played with all the pets at 4th level and found the fire pet to be the most usefull for solo exp'ing. I only used the earth pet when I needed mobs rooted which isn't the typical situation for me.<br>
<br>
I used the fire pet mainly again and water pet w/fire dam shield occasionally for poison mobs, at 8th lev.    Now at 13 I'm just using my fire pet, and didn't bother with the other pet spells at 4pp ea.<br>
<br>
As the costs go up for higher level pets and or difficulty with research issues, is there a particular level where all the pets have equal value or utility and therefore warrant the cost/labor of having all 4 pets available?<br>
<br>
Petmeister<br>
Gnomish Mage of 13 Sprockets  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=variathemage>Varia the mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 148<br> <font color=#333333>(1/13/03 12:33:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=934.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: At what level is it worthwhile to maintain all four pets</span><hr size=1> /shrug<br>
<br>
I hit 50 by using water and fire and no other pets other than to test them out.  In the 50s, I started switching between three types of pets.  Just find which type you like the most and make sure you always have the newest spell of that type.  If you have some spare money, then it might be nice to have one or two other types for situations where your favorite isn't very useful.  The main benefit of having all four types is when you need a pet that is highly resistant to a certain spell type such as cold, poison, etc.<br>
<br>
As a side note, levels 8 through the early 20s are when spells are the hardest to afford.  By the 20s, you are finally making enough money to be able to afford your spells and you can start looking at buying some equipment in addition to your spells.<br>
<br>
Edit: Oh, I forgot to add that as your pets get higher in level, their strengths and weaknesses become more apparent.  Earth pets are supposed to have the most HP, but at level 8 the difference isn't all that great.  By 49 the difference is huge. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=108671">Varia Darselai</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Arch Convoker</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=variathemage>Varia the mage</A> at: 1/13/03 12:38:12 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 849<br> <font color=#333333>(1/13/03 3:22:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=934.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: At what level is it worthwhile to maintain all four pets</span><hr size=1> For soloing non-casters, the air pet would be probably the lowest priority until level 53.  <br>
<br>
Until 24, Water would be your most useful solo pet.  At that point Fire becomes your biggest priority.  Earth starts coming into its own around level 39.<br>
<br>
If you primarily group for experience, Air would probably be your best bet overall, unless you need heavier damage.  In groups, water will slightly outdamage fire pets unless the pet is tanking.<br>
<br>
If you mix your styles and hunting grounds a lot, then being diverse will be to your benefit.  If not, focus your attention on the pets that benefit you the most and don't worry much about the rest.<br>
<br>
As an aside, post-50 it will be to your benefit to get the full range of pets.  Earth typically for chaining, Air for tanking/grouping, Fire for stunning, Water for heavy (backstab) damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2645<br> <font color=#333333>(1/13/03 10:59:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=934.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: At what level is it worthwhile to maintain all four pets</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Fire for stunning<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I have yet to find the post-50 fire pet useful, and have never seen one that reliably stunned.<br>
