<br>
Don't rely on one pet.  All pets have their advantages and when you are a low level mage it's time for you to experiment and find out what pet you like for what SPECIFIC situation.<br>
<br>
DON'T cop-out and just cast 1 pet for the next 4-5 levels.  Try them all and try them in different situations.  That's what being a good mage is all about.  You need to learn what pet you like where, when, and why.  As you become more skilled at playing your toon, you'll have a good feeling what pet will be the best.  <br>
<br>
A better question to have asked would be &quot;this is where I'm hunting, and this is the mob I'm killing, what pet would work best and why.&quot;<br>
<br>
I remember fighting snakes at level 13.  Water pet was simply the best because it always resisted the poison spells.  When I hunted rat's that diseased, I used the earth pet.  When I was fighting mobs that hit fast for low damage, fire pet owned.  Take the time and learn EACH of these pet characterisics and when to apply them.  It will make you a better player. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Master Eandori Raintree<br>
