For soloing non-casters, the air pet would be probably the lowest priority until level 53. <br>
<br>
Personally I disagree completely.  From about 28 to 51 the air pet was my soloing pet of choice unless something dictated a different pet (must-have root, poison resistance, fire resistance or whatever).  The air pet can tank as well as the earth or water due to its high agility/ac and as it does not root it does not take damage from low-hp mobs trying to flee.  The stun gives you a chance to flee if the mob want you rather than the pet.  It is also excellent in groups as the stun mitigates damage to the tank.  Finally, if the mob is totally MR the air pet casts less frequently than the others so misses less melee rounds!<br>
<br>
For 51 &amp; 52 I generally used earth but at 53 I went back to air until 57.  Now I am impatient for 59 - I want my air pet back!!  To be honest, on mobs which want to flee and can be allowed to, I'm not convinced the 57 earth is much superior to the 53 air - it does more DPS but also takes a LOT more. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lobaner>Lobaner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#333333>(1/15/03 12:48:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=934.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: At what level is it worthwhile to maintain all four pets</span><hr size=1> Only by nurturing your relationship with all four elements can you attain mastery and realize the power that is mage!<br>
